Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim @carrot{3%oz}; using a #peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core. Discard core. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and remove strings from @sugar snap peas{4%oz}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{5%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{¾%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, and @salt{pinch}; set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and up to half the @sriracha{1%tsp} (save the rest for serving).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add carrot and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add zucchini and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl with carrot.

Add snap peas and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, undisturbed, until charred on one side, ~{1-2%minutes}. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and charred all over, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to bowl with veggies. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, you may want to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{2}. Arrange carrot, zucchini, and snap peas on top. Top each bowl with a fried egg and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Drizzle with sauce and any remaining sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

> The only thing more fun than saying "bibimbap"? Eating it! This riff on the classic Korean rice bowl is positively bursting with flavorful veggies. Sweet carrot ribbons, tender zucchini, lightly charred snap peas, and pickled scallions are arranged over a bed of steamy rice, just waiting to be mixed up and dug into. But not so fast! The bowl gets drizzled with an addictive sesame-Sriracha-soy sauce, then crowned with our favorite bowl topper: a perfectly fried egg.